2.text: If it is an oily stain, avoid using water.

3.text: If it not an oily stain, rinse with cold water.
3.vid: /8/83/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 3 Version 2.360p.mp4

4.text: Apply stain remover to the stain.
4.vid: /f/f3/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 4 Version 4.360p.mp4

5.text: Place it in your washing machine.

6.text: Obtain hydrogen peroxide and dishwashing liquid.
6.vid: /1/1a/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 6 Version 4.360p.mp4

7.text: Mix the liquid together and pour it into a spray bottle.
7.vid: /a/a1/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 7 Version 4.360p.mp4

8.vid: /2/26/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 8 Version 4.360p.mp4

9.text: Spray the cleaner directly onto the stain.
9.vid: /6/60/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 9 Version 4.360p.mp4

10.text: Consider soaking it for larger or stubborn stains.
10.vid: /a/a5/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 10 Version 2.360p.mp4

11.vid: /8/84/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 11 Version 4.360p.mp4

12.vid: /d/d0/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 12 Version 4.360p.mp4

14.text: Use white chalk for an oily stain.
14.vid: /d/d6/Get Stains out of White Clothes Step 14 Version 4.360p.mp4

15.text: Differentiate between oxidizing and chlorine bleaches.

16.text: Use bleach to spot clean persistent stains.
